course_description: This course introduces concepts in evaluation and management of patients across the lifespan in pre-hospital, urgent and emergency care settings.  Emphasis on evidence-based practice, clinical decision making, interdisciplinary communication, interpreting diagnostic tests and obtaining advanced practice competencies.
prerequisites: NRSG 753D as prerequisite, NRSG 754D and NRSG 755D as corequisites, or equivalent transfer credit.
